panel.description:
Add a gsmnode item to the Home Assistant sidebar, opening one of the gateway's own overviews.

API Server panel: {api_base}
Web App: {web_app}

Leave the address empty to use the one above for the chosen overview. Set it when Home Assistant, your browser and the API Server disagree about how to reach a service — behind a reverse proxy or a VPN, for instance.

events.description:
Pick what the gateway should tell Home Assistant about. Each one arrives as an event on the bus that an automation can trigger on — build one under Settings → Automations, choose the Event trigger, and give it the event type.

Current selection fires: {fired}

Home Assistant registers a webhook of its own for this and subscribes it with the gateway; nothing has to be registered by hand, and unticking everything removes the subscription again.
